{"id": "1437546623243780178", "channel_id": "1437523323868287138", "type": 0, "author_id": "195401302145105920", "author_name": "jollysquire", "author_bot": false, "content": "Leap (and Quasar) is a keyword, letting you know that if it is the first card played in a round, it will have changed effects (or additional effects for Quasar). \n\nSpecifically in Daffodil's case for example, if Skull Reaver is the first card played that round, it will deal DMG to the HIGHEST HP enemy. If it is not the first card played it will deal DMG to the LOWEST HP enemy instead.", "timestamp": "2025-11-10T20:57:03.306000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-11-10T20:59:21.295000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "🙏", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1437523323868287138", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "What is the \"Leap\" of Lady Daffodil? How can it be used? It's on some of her cards.", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747489132412979"]}
